    ‚ąá make1 args;rc;msg;char;t
      :Access public
      :Implements constructor
    ‚ćĚ args is one of
    ‚ćĚ - a simple character vector which is the name of a configuration file
    ‚ćĚ - a reference to a namespace containing named configuration settings
    ‚ćĚ - a depth 1 or 2 vector of
    ‚ćĚ   [1] integer port to listen on
    ‚ćĚ   [2] charvec function folder or ref to code location
    ‚ćĚ   [3] paradigm to use ('JSON' or 'REST')
      MakeCommon
      :If char‚ÜźisChar args ‚ćĚ character argument?  it's either config filename or CodeLocation folder
          :If ~‚éēNEXISTS args
              ‚Üí0‚ä£Log'Unable to find "',args,'"'
          :ElseIf 2=t‚Üź1 ‚éēNINFO args ‚ćĚ normal file
              :If (lc‚äĘ/‚éēNPARTS args)‚ąä'.json' '.json5' ‚ćĚ json files are configuration
                  :If 0‚Č†‚äÉ(rc msg)‚ÜźLoadConfiguration JarvisConfig‚Üźargs
                      Log'Error loading configuration: ',msg
                  :EndIf
              :Else
                  CodeLocation‚Üźargs ‚ćĚ might be a namespace script or class
              :EndIf
          :ElseIf 1=t ‚ćĚ folder means it's CodeLocation
              CodeLocation‚Üźargs
          :Else ‚ćĚ not a file or folder
              Log'Invalid constructor argument "',args,'"'
          :EndIf
      :ElseIf 9.1={‚éēNC‚äā,'‚ćĶ'}args ‚ćĚ namespace?
          :If 0‚Č†‚äÉ(rc msg)‚ÜźLoadConfiguration args
              Log'Error loading configuration: ',msg
          :EndIf
      :Else
          :If 326=‚éēDR args
          :AndIf 0‚ąß.=‚Č°¬®2‚ÜĎargs   ‚ćĚ if 2‚ÜĎargs is (port ref) (both scalar)
              args[1]‚Üź‚äā,args[1] ‚ćĚ nest port so ‚ąádefault works properly
          :EndIf
     
          (Port CodeLocation Paradigm JarvisConfig)‚Üźargs default Port CodeLocation Paradigm JarvisConfig
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

