‚ćĚ The following is commented out because it seems the GnuTLS knows to use the operating system's certificate collection even on non-Windows platforms
‚ćĚ          :ElseIf ~isWin
‚ćĚ              ‚Üí‚ąÜEXIT‚ä£(rc msg)‚Üź¬Į1 'No RootCertDir spcified'
          :EndIf
          :If 0‚ąä‚ćīServerCertSKI ‚ćĚ no certificate ID specified, check for Cert and Key files
              ‚Üí‚ąÜEXIT If(rc msg)‚Üź'ServerCertFile'Exists ServerCertFile
              ‚Üí‚ąÜEXIT If(rc msg)‚Üź'ServerKeyFile'Exists ServerKeyFile
